Hello,

I had to disable VIDEO_WAYLAND or SDL would not compile (see [this issue](https://github.com/pisto/sdos-test/commit/3726520a1747d0db48d054ba62e4bb322355cca3)). Afterwards I had to modify the sources of the collada module and the convex decomposition module because of obvious faults in the code:

```
diff --git a/Engine/lib/collada/src/dae/daeMetaGroup.cpp b/Engine/lib/collada/src/dae/daeMetaGroup.cpp
index 0beb671..f517034 100644
--- a/Engine/lib/collada/src/dae/daeMetaGroup.cpp
+++ b/Engine/lib/collada/src/dae/daeMetaGroup.cpp
@@ -31,7 +31,7 @@ daeElement *daeMetaGroup::placeElement( daeElement *parent, daeElement *child, d
        (void)offset;
        daeString nm = child->getElementName();
        if ( findChild( nm ) == NULL ) {
-               return false;
+               return NULL;
        }
        daeElementRef el;

diff --git a/Engine/lib/convexDecomp/NvHashMap.h b/Engine/lib/convexDecomp/NvHashMap.h
index 3d57da0..c8dfd78 100644
--- a/Engine/lib/convexDecomp/NvHashMap.h
+++ b/Engine/lib/convexDecomp/NvHashMap.h
@@ -692,9 +692,6 @@ namespace CONVEX_DECOMPOSITION
                                mCapacity = t.mCapacity;

                                copy(mData,t.mData,t.mSize);
-                               mSize = t.mSize;
-
-                               return;
                        }
                        else
                        {
@@ -1521,7 +1518,7 @@ namespace CONVEX_DECOMPOSITION
                        NX_INLINE const Entry *find(const Key &k) const
                        {
                                if(!mHash.size())
-                                       return false;
+                                       return NULL;

                                NxU32 h = hash(k);
                                NxU32 index = mHash[h];
```

Then it worked. I don't know why someone would use this return; statement in NvHashMap. It seems pretty illogical, since the data has been copied and *this can be returned again. Also the mSize will be set after the whole if to t.mSize, no reason to do it inside this branch.

Apply it with the patch tool with -p1 (I didn't let git diff remove the a/, b/ prefixes).

Named textures don't work with translucent materials, though they work with diffuse materials using the deferred rendering pipeline. For example:

1) Make something with a named texture. e.g. an offscreen canvas:

```
new GuiOffscreenCanvas(TestCanvas) {
    dynamicTarget = true;
    targetName = "myCanvasTexture";
    targetSize = "1024 1024";
};

TestCanvas.setContent(MainMenuGui);
```

2) Use the named texture in a material:

```
singleton Material(TestCanvasMaterial)
{
    diffuseMap[0] = "#myCanvasTexture";
};
```

3) Use the material on an object, e.g. the default grid:

```
GroundPlane.Material = TestCanvasMaterial;
```

4) You should now see canvas content on the ground plane. However when you set the material as translucent, the texture is replaced by the fallback "No Texture" texture:

```
TestCanvasMaterial.translucent = 1;
TestCanvasMaterial.translucentBlendOp = "LerpAlpha";
TestCanvasMaterial.reload();
```

What should happen is the named texture should work with the diffuse map of the material regardless of the underlying rendering mode.
